## Quick Start

### Running with Fake Interface (Testing)

```bash
pip install -e ".[dev]"
python src/{{ module_name }}_rest_node.py --fake
curl http://localhost:{{ port }}/health
```

### Available Actions

| Action | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| `measure` | Take a measurement reading |
| `calibrate` | Calibrate the instrument |
| `get_instrument_status` | Get current instrument status |
| `reset_instrument` | Reset to initial state |

### Using the Interface Directly

```python
from {{ module_name }}_interface import {{ module_name | pascal_case }}Interface

interface = {{ module_name | pascal_case }}Interface()
interface.connect()
interface.initialize()

reading = interface.measure(channel="ch1")
print(f"Value: {reading.value} {reading.units}")

interface.shutdown()
interface.disconnect()
```

